The paper presents a classification model for multi-class boosting in machine learning and computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses its experimental results on challenging multi-class machine learning and vision tasks, indicating that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well. The paper proposes a scalable and effective approach to multi-class boosting, which involves optimization and parameter tuning, suggesting that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the approach, indicating that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
